-- #171, `intBoundFor` arm: 2^62 as a pattern RANGE bound. Third distinct
-- rejection site (the range hi-bound is parsed by `intBound`, not by
-- `parseAtomRaw` or `parsePatAtom`). Untested, this silently becomes the range
-- `0..intMinBound` — an EMPTY range that matches nothing, with no diagnostic.
-- The negated bound stays legal and is covered by the accept fixture in
-- run_check_agreement_fixtures/accept_int_lit_min_bound.
f n = match n
  0..4611686018427387904 => 1
  _ => 0

main = println (f 1)
